President Muhammadu Buhari is will be departing Abuja on Wednesday on a 20-day vacation in the United Kingdom (UK).
The Presidency in a statement on Sunday indicated that President Buhari is expected to depart  Nigeria on Wednesday, explaining further that the President will depart UK after the 20-day vacation for Riyadh, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, to attend the Third Summit, thereafter, depart for Austria for the World Economic Summit,  while he is expected back to Nigeria on April 4.
The presidency statement reads in part:
“Also, at the end of the summit, President Buhari will on 2nd March depart Saudi Arabia to Austria for World Economic Summit.
“President Buhari is expected back in Nigeria on 04th April 2020″.










			
